  "prompt": "How much does it cost to attend a TED talk?",
  "response": "The cost to attend a TED talk can vary significantly depending on the specific event. TEDx events, which are independently organized but follow the TED format, often charge a nominal fee that can range from free to a few hundred dollars, depending on the venue and organizers.\n\nOn the other hand, attending the main TED Conference in Vancouver typically involves a much higher cost. Ticket prices for this event can range from several thousand dollars, sometimes exceeding $10,000. Additionally, there may be extra costs for accommodation, travel, and other expenses associated with attending.\n\nIt's best to check the official TED website or the specific event's website for the most accurate and up-to-date pricing information.",
